To implement the shopping cart functionality, we need to:
1. Add a `ShoppingCart` model to manage the cart items.
2. Create controller endpoints for adding products to the shopping cart, viewing the shopping cart, and handling session persistence.
3. Handle session management for both logged-in users and guest users.

We will extend our existing folder structure to support the new shopping cart functionality.

## Final Project Folder Structure:
my_project/
├── backend/
│   ├── models/
│   │   ├── user_model.py
│   │   ├── password_reset_model.py
│   │   ├── product_model.py
│   │   ├── category_model.py
│   │   ├── shopping_cart_model.py
│   ├── views/
│   │   ├── user_view.py
│   ├── controllers/
│   │   ├── user_controller.py
│   │   ├── password_reset_controller.py
│   │   ├── profile_controller.py
│   │   ├── product_controller.py
│   │   ├── category_controller.py
│   │   ├── shopping_cart_controller.py
├── database/
│   ├── schema.sql
├── app.py
├── requirements.txt

